#998
@@WSilver Marketwalk@@N~
The marketwalk on this tier bears no trace of the silver trade, its shops selling everyday necessities like soap, nails, and cheap crockery to the surrounding residential blocks. A delivery cart loaded with firewood bundles is often parked outside the fuel merchant's premises, forcing pedestrians to step into the gutter to pass. The old tariff board survives on the wall, though it has been papered over with neighbourhood announcements and is no longer legible beneath its layers of handbills.

