#999
@@WCrimson Concourse@@N~
The concourse on this tier has fully transitioned from its martial origins to a quiet residential street where the only reminder of the militia is an old recruiting poster faded to near-illegibility on a rain-streaked wall. Children play in the wider spots of the walkway, and a grandmother sits knitting in a doorway, keeping half an eye on their games. The pavement here is worn smooth and slightly sunken in the center where generations of foot traffic have compressed the stone.

