#1000
@@WAuburn Traverse@@N~
The amber brick facing has given way entirely to plain stone on this tier, though a few courses of the original warm-toned brick survive near the roofline as a reminder of the traverse's former character. A rain barrel collects runoff from a sagging gutter pipe, its water used by residents for washing. The traverse here is wide enough for a single cart, and wheel ruts in the cobbles show the path that delivery wagons follow when supplying the corner provisions shop.

