#1001
@@WBronze Colonnade@@N~
The bronze columns on this tier are the shortest and most weathered of the series, their verdigris coating thick and uneven. The institutional offices have been replaced by practical services: a public laundry, a municipal clinic, and a records archive whose shelves are visible through barred windows. The colonnade provides shelter during rain, and chalk marks on the pavement show where vendors set up temporary stalls during the brief afternoon market.

