#1002
@@WSunward Way@@N~
The limestone has darkened to a uniform grey on this tier, indistinguishable from the common stone used elsewhere in the lower city. A fountain supplied by the temple district water system provides a focal point for the block, its stone basin carved with a simple geometric design that predates the Lantern Reforms. Residents queue here in the mornings to fill water jugs, exchanging neighbourhood gossip while they wait for their turn at the spout.

