#1003
@@WMarble Ring@@N~
No marble survives on this tier, the name persisting only through civic habit and the faded lettering on a corner building that reads "Marble Ring" in old-fashioned script. The buildings here are solid working-class construction, their stone walls thick and their windows small, designed for warmth retention rather than light. A tallow chandler operates from the ground floor of the corner lot, and the waxy, slightly acrid smell of rendered fat permeates the block.

