#1005
@@WGranite Arcade@@N~
The arcade on this tier has been fully enclosed, its pillars incorporated into the building walls and its former walkway converted into a row of small shops. A cobbler, a cup-maker, and a vendor of cheap ink and paper share the converted space, their businesses separated by thin wooden partitions that do little to contain the mixed smells. The granite is still visible in places where the newer construction has not covered it, its surface bearing the weathered remains of Founding-era carved marks.

