#1006
@@WSaffron Walk@@N~
The walk has lost even the whitewash of the tier above, its stone walls left bare and grey. A cat sleeps in a sunny patch on the pavement, undisturbed by the occasional pedestrian. The saint's niche tradition persists at this depth in the city grid, though the carved figure here is a crude replacement carved by a neighbourhood resident after the original was stolen, and the candle offerings are irregular and sparse.

