#1007
@@WAzure Plaza@@N~
This tier's open space functions less as a plaza and more as a neighbourhood courtyard, surrounded by residential buildings whose residents use it for drying laundry and as a play area for children. A hand-pump well in the center provides the block's primary water supply, its iron handle squeaking with each stroke. The blue-grey slate has been entirely replaced with common paving, and only the name, remembered by long-time residents, connects this space to the grander plazas above.

