#1008
@@WEmber Court@@N~
The court on this tier has cooled entirely, its forge-era identity surviving only in the darkened stone and the residual warmth trapped in the thick walls of buildings originally designed to withstand furnace heat. A small tavern occupies the corner, serving cheap ale and bread to the working residents of the lower wards, its sign depicting a hammer and anvil in faded paint. The cobbles here retain their sooty character, though the source is now chimney smoke rather than forge scale.

