@@WGilded Crossing@@N~
This crossing has become a purely functional intersection with no trace of its former mercantile grandeur. The buildings are plain and practical, their doors unmarked except for painted house numbers, and the foot traffic consists entirely of residents going about daily errands. A public notice board on the corner post carries neighbourhood watch schedules and municipal announcements, its surface covered with layers of overlapping handbills.

