@@WIron Byway@@N~
The reinforced architecture of the Fortification Era gives this tier's byway a bunker-like solidity, with thick walls and low ceilings that muffle street noise and create a sense of enclosed quiet. The former emergency stores have been divided into small apartments, their heavy iron doors now propped open with wedges to admit light and air. The iron-strip pavement reinforcement has been partially pulled up for scrap, leaving irregular grooves in the stone that collect rainwater.

