@@WViolet Terrace@@N~
The terrace identity has been entirely absorbed into the surrounding streetscape on this tier, the violet-grey stone indistinguishable from the general building material under its coating of city grime. A retired lamplighter has turned his ground-floor rooms into an informal repair shop, fixing broken lanterns and selling reconditioned wicks to the neighbourhood. The lavender planters of the upper tiers are a distant memory here, replaced by practical window boxes growing kitchen herbs.

