@@WVerdant Causeway@@N~
The vine trellises on this tier support only a few scraggly survivors of the dense growth found above, their bare iron framework visible against the stone walls like the ribs of a dormant organism. The community garden has given way to a patch of hard-packed earth where residents stack firewood for the winter. The causeway remains greener than the fully-paved streets around it, however, thanks to moss growing in the mortar joints and a persistent clump of grass pushing through a crack in the pavement.

