#1013
@@WObsidian Crescent@@N~
The obsidian crescent reaches its darkest and quietest on this tier, where the widely-spaced lamps leave long pools of shadow and the foot traffic thins to occasional residents moving between home and the corner shops. The volcanic stone has been partially covered by plaster in places where building owners tried to brighten the block, but the plaster has peeled away in sheets, revealing the black stone beneath in ragged patches. The crescent's curve is tightest here, almost doubling back on itself before straightening into the eastern wards.

