@@yThe Western Gate@@N~
The broad stone arch of @@WMidgaard@@N's western gate stands at the formal terminus of the sixth ring, its iron-banded doors open during daylight and monitored by a permanent guard detail at all hours. The pavement beneath the arch is worn by the heavy passage of wagons on the @@yRoc Road@@N, and carved distance markers in the gatehouse walls indicate the leagues to the principal western destinations. Travel advisories posted beside the gate warn of road conditions and known hazards along the western route toward Kiess, updated weekly by the Road Warden Liaison stationed here. The gate's keystone bears the city's seal flanked by the @@ydouble wheel@@N of the Cartwright's Compact, symbols of the commercial traffic that built this quarter.

