@@WSilver Marketwalk@@N~
The institutional character of the sixth ring dominates here, with the former market shops converted into clerks' offices and public document repositories. A stone-carved directory mounted on the wall lists the departments housed in the surrounding buildings, their names abbreviated in civic shorthand that only regular visitors can parse. The foot traffic is orderly and purposeful, the pace set by clerks carrying document boxes between departments. Steps to the south descend into the commercial quarter, where the ring of steel and the smell of leather from the armory district carry up through the entrance passage.

