@@WCrimson Concourse@@N~
The concourse on this tier serves as the approach to the institutional quarter's central offices, its stone facades bearing the carved seals of various municipal departments. A pair of flag brackets project from the wall above, flying the city's white-and-gold standard on official days. The foot traffic here includes a mix of government clerks, supplicants bearing petitions, and the occasional temple functionary crossing between the religious quarter and the civic administration. The concourse's southern end opens toward the outfitting quarter below, where the clean cedar scent of the clothiers' workshops drifts up through the passage.

