#1020
@@WAuburn Traverse@@N~
The traverse on this tier has been widened by the demolition of a row of old shops, creating a small forecourt in front of a registry building whose doors stand open during business hours. A queue of citizens waiting for permit stamps snakes across the forecourt on busy days, their patience tested by the slow pace of the bureaucratic process within. The brick facing that gives the traverse its name survives only on the registry building itself, preserved by municipal order as a historical feature. A passage to the south leads into the arcane district below, where the faint scent of spell reagents and the glow of magefire globes mark the shops of the arcane supply trade.

