@@WBronze Colonnade@@N~
The colonnade on the institutional tier has been restored to its original appearance, the verdigris cleaned from the bronze columns and their surfaces polished to a warm golden-brown. The restoration was undertaken as a civic pride project, and a small plaque at the base of one column records the names of the donors who funded the work. The ground-floor offices behind the colonnade house the city's land registry and property tribunal, and their doors bear brass nameplates in the formal civic style. The colonnade's southern aspect opens toward the provisioners' quarter below, where supply depots and expedition outfitters cater to those preparing for long journeys from the city.

