@@WSunward Way@@N~
Sunward Way on the institutional tier opens onto a small park-like space where a cluster of shade trees has been allowed to grow in a cobbled planter, their canopy providing welcome shade during summer and a framework for festival lanterns during the winter solstice celebrations. A cafe operates from a ground-floor room facing the trees, its tables set outside when weather permits, serving tea and simple meals to the clerks and temple staff who frequent this block. The fountain from the tier above is fed by the same pipe system, though the basin here is larger and decorated with carved fish. A passage to the south leads down into the military district, where the city's invasion quartermaster operates a standing depot under emergency charter authority.

