@@WMarble Ring@@N~
The institutional tier restores something of the marble ring's original character, with fresh-cut white stone facing the civic buildings that line this stretch. A memorial wall occupies the gap between two department buildings, its surface covered with the carved names of citizens who died in the city's defense during the Fortification Era. Fresh flowers and small oil lamps are placed at the wall's base on memorial days, maintained by a volunteer committee of war veterans and their families. The ring's southern arm leads down into the quest district, where commission boards and chartered contracts draw seekers from across the region.

