@@WGolden Mews@@N~
The mews on this tier has been incorporated into the temple district's service infrastructure, housing the workshops where temple furnishings are repaired and liturgical supplies prepared. The smell of beeswax and incense replaces the metalworking odours of the upper tiers, and the artisans here work with the careful, unhurried pace of people whose output is measured by quality rather than quantity. Gilded temple ornaments in various stages of restoration are visible through the workshop windows. A passage to the south leads down toward the brokers' district, where bounty postings and expedition commissions are administered by licensed agents under civic seal.

