One of the Lantern Registry's route-workers, this lamplighter follows a chalk-marked circuit that has been walked every watch cycle since the Lantern Reforms first mapped it. A leather satchel hangs from one shoulder, weighted with oil flasks and spare wick-stock, and a long brass hook pole serves as both tool and walking staff. The faint smell of lamp oil clings to everything they wear.

