a day-mark laborer~
A laborer moves through the street with the trudging gait of someone who has been working since first light.

~
Day-mark laborers are the backbone of @@WMidgaard@@N's manual economy: registered workers who receive stamped day tokens each morning and are paid by the circuit. Their token must match the day's stamp at the Registry gate or they are classed as shadow residents â undocumented and outside civic protection. The tired set of this one's shoulders suggests the token today came late.

~
