~
The Edge and Iron blademaster carries the particular stillness of someone who has survived enough fights to stop needing to announce it. The worn fighting leathers are maintained to working condition rather than showroom standard, and the calluses on both hands are the informational kind that customers read before asking prices. A short evaluation usually happens when someone walks in: posture, weapon hand, movement pattern. The blademaster does not comment on the assessment but it informs whether they lead with the catalog or the custom fitting bench.
~
